page.title: 04ENDERBY
page.content: In Enderby there are many terraced houses,but they are mainly in the central streets.Round the outskirts are mainly semi-detached houses and some council houses. In Enderby there are shops selling consumer durables like carpets and motorbikes.Enderby has different shops from Narborough and Whetstone. The oldest part has thatched cottages which are on top of a hill. Enderby is hilly and bumpy.It has its own leisure centre.Enderby is busy but it is a dull place as well.It is bigger than both Narborough and Whetstone.
